# 🇯🇵 **RINBAN (BoJ JGB PURCHASE OPERATIONS) — THE REAL CONTROL KNOB**

![Image](https://www.boj.or.jp/en/research/brp/fsr/img/fsr241024c.png)

![Image](https://cloudfront-us-east-2.images.arcpublishing.com/reuters/OJGUGOEFXZJGJB2YFGSRNHNLGE.jpg)

![Image](https://libertystreeteconomics.newyorkfed.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/06/6a01348793456c970c0263e94e43b8200b-500wi.jpg)

**Rinban (輪番)** refers to the **Bank of Japan’s regular, maturity-specific JGB purchase operations**.
It is the *day-to-day implementation tool* of Japan’s monetary policy.

> **YCC defines the destination.
> Rinban controls the road and the speed.**

---

## 1️⃣ WHAT EXACTLY IS RINBAN?

Rinban = **scheduled BoJ outright purchases of JGBs**, split by maturity buckets:

Typical buckets:

* **1–3Y**
* **3–5Y**
* **5–10Y**
* **10–25Y**
* **25Y+**

Each operation specifies:

* Maturity bucket
* Purchase amount (¥bn)
* Frequency

These are announced in advance but **adjusted constantly**.

---

## 2️⃣ WHY RINBAN MATTERS MORE THAN THE POLICY RATE

Japan’s policy rate moves rarely and slowly.
Rinban moves **weekly, sometimes daily**.

### In practice:

* A ¥100bn change in Rinban can move **10Y yields more than a rate hike**
* Markets infer policy intent from **which bucket** is adjusted, not just size

**This is why Rinban is Japan’s “shadow policy rate.”**

---

## 3️⃣ RINBAN vs YCC (CRITICAL DISTINCTION)

| Tool       | What it does                                    | Market meaning   |
| ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- | ---------------- |
| **YCC**    | Sets the *maximum tolerated yield level*        | Long-term anchor |
| **Rinban** | Controls *liquidity & pressure* along the curve | Tactical signal  |

Think of YCC as the **ceiling**, and Rinban as **how hard the BoJ leans on the market before the ceiling is hit**.

---

## 4️⃣ HOW RINBAN TRANSMITS INTO MARKETS

![Image](https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i5EJ61xce1wY/v2/pidjEfPlU1QWZop3vfGKsrX.ke8XuWirGYh1PKgEw44kE/-1x-1.png)

![Image](https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5612AQFWOb3GDQHFWQ/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/0/1673599588064?e=2147483647\&t=eksTV0DSa_3yLWPZtHFr6JPgAJ0k1TRrm_ynK9D1Uuk\&v=beta)

![Image](https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/%24s_%21RUol%21%2Cf_auto%2Cq_auto%3Agood%2Cfl_progressive%3Asteep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce0ee64-e859-4cf8-a5d6-b893ab190af3_472x420.png)

### 🟢 Increase Rinban

BoJ buys **more bonds** in a maturity bucket.

**Effects:**

* Yields ↓ (or stop rising)
* Liquidity ↓ (BoJ removes float)
* Repo specialness ↑
* Futures basis widens
* FX impact: **JPY weakens** (policy seen as dovish)

### 🔴 Reduce Rinban

BoJ buys **less bonds**.

**Effects:**

* Yields ↑
* Liquidity ↑
* Market functioning improves
* Volatility ↑
* FX impact: **JPY strengthens** (stealth tightening)

---

## 5️⃣ WHICH RINBAN BUCKET MATTERS MOST?

### 🔹 5–10Y Rinban (MOST IMPORTANT)

* This is where **YCC pressure concentrates**
* Reduction here = **de facto normalization**
* Traders see this as permission for 10Y yields to rise

> If 5–10Y Rinban is cut → **market tests the implicit ceiling**

---

### 🔹 10–25Y & 25Y+ Rinban

* Controls **curve steepness**
* Cuts here → long-end sells off → **steepeners**
* BoJ watches super-long vol as a *financial stability gauge*

---

### 🔹 Short-end Rinban (1–3Y, 3–5Y)

* Mostly technical
* Rarely used as a signaling tool
* Used to manage excess reserves & repo conditions

---

## 6️⃣ RINBAN & IMPLICIT CEILINGS (HOW MARKETS READ IT)

Markets do **not** wait for a YCC announcement.

They watch:

* First: **Rinban reductions**
* Then: yield creep
* Then: test of the ceiling

### Typical sequence:

1. BoJ **reduces 5–10Y Rinban**
2. 10Y yield drifts higher
3. Volatility increases
4. Market probes implicit ceiling
5. BoJ either:

   * Defends (fixed-rate ops), or
   * Resets regime (widen band / remove YCC)

This is how **policy changes are smuggled into the market quietly**.

---

## 7️⃣ RINBAN & LIQUIDITY (THE UNDERAPPRECIATED EFFECT)

When BoJ buys aggressively:

* JGB float shrinks
* Dealers struggle to make markets
* Liquidity collapses
* Volatility paradoxically rises

So:

> **More Rinban = less liquidity, not more**

This is why BoJ sometimes **cuts Rinban to improve market functioning**, even if it allows yields to rise.

---

## 8️⃣ RINBAN → FX TRANSMISSION (VERY IMPORTANT)

### Dovish Rinban (more buying):

* Yields capped
* Rate differentials widen vs US
* USDJPY ↑
* Carry trades thrive

### Hawkish Rinban (less buying):

* Yields drift higher
* Rate differential narrows
* USDJPY ↓
* JPY strengthens even *without* rate hikes

This is how Japan tightens **without touching the policy rate**.

---

## 9️⃣ HOW TRADERS USE RINBAN (DESK PLAYBOOK)

### 🧠 Signal extraction

* Watch **5–10Y bucket changes** first
* Ignore headline “total purchase amount”
* Compare to previous ops, not expectations

### 📈 Trades

* **Rinban cut (5–10Y)** →

  * Short 10Y JGB
  * 10s30s steepener
  * Short USDJPY

* **Rinban increase** →

  * Long JGBs
  * Flatteners
  * Long USDJPY

* **Erratic Rinban changes** →

  * Buy JGB volatility

---

